cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL

The paper deals with action recognition in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves the use of probabilistic inference, which is also a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation is done on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper involves the use of regularizing priors, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
